casebody.data:
STATE of Missouri, Respondent,
v.
D'Chaun Diablo NEBBITT, Appellant. WD 81224 Missouri Court of Appeals, Western District. ORDER FILED: November 20, 2018 Robert J. (Jeff) Bartholomew, Jefferson City, MO, for respondent. Samuel Buffaloe, Columbia, MO, for appellant. Before Division Three: Gary D. Witt, Presiding Judge, Cynthia L. Martin, Judge and Anthony Rex Gabbert, Judge

ORDER

Per curiam:

D'Chaun Nebbitt appeals from a judgment convicting him of felony stealing. In his sole point on appeal, Nebbitt argues that the trial court abused its discretion by overruling defense counsel's request to place the "not guilty" verdict form before the "guilty" verdict form. Finding no error, we affirm. Rule 30.25(b).
